sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant GW as Gateway API<br/>(HTTPRoute)
    participant API as batch-gateway-apiserver<br/>API Port HTTP/HTTPS
    participant PG as PostgreSQL<br/>5432/TCP
    participant Redis as Redis/Valkey<br/>6379/TCP
    participant FS as File Store<br/>(S3 :443 / FS)
    participant Proc as batch-gateway-processor
    participant LLM as LLM Inference Gateway<br/>(llm-d / vLLM)
    participant GC as batch-gateway-gc

    Note over Client,LLM: Flow 1: Batch Job Submission and Execution

    Client->>GW: POST /v1/files (multipart JSONL)<br/>Tenant: X-MaaS-Username
    GW->>API: Forward request
    API->>FS: Upload input file<br/>HTTPS/TLS (S3) or local FS
    FS-->>API: File stored (file_id)
    API->>PG: Store file metadata<br/>TCP/TLS
    PG-->>API: Confirmed
    API-->>Client: 200 OK {file_id}

    Client->>GW: POST /v1/batches<br/>{input_file_id, model, endpoint}<br/>Tenant: X-MaaS-Username
    GW->>API: Forward request
    API->>PG: Create batch record<br/>TCP/TLS
    PG-->>API: Confirmed (batch_id)
    API->>Redis: Enqueue to priority queue<br/>(sorted set, SLO priority)<br/>TCP/TLS
    Redis-->>API: Enqueued
    API-->>Client: 200 OK {batch_id, status: validating}

    Proc->>Redis: BLMPOP dequeue job<br/>(semaphore-driven polling)<br/>TCP/TLS
    Redis-->>Proc: Job payload
    Proc->>FS: Download input JSONL<br/>HTTPS/TLS (S3) or local
    FS-->>Proc: Input file content
    Proc->>Redis: Update status: in_progress<br/>TCP/TLS

    loop For each request in JSONL (concurrent, semaphore-limited)
        Proc->>LLM: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>Auth: Bearer token<br/>HTTP/HTTPS TLS 1.2+
        LLM-->>Proc: Inference response
        Proc->>Redis: Update progress counter<br/>TCP/TLS
    end

    Proc->>FS: Upload output JSONL<br/>HTTPS/TLS (S3) or local
    FS-->>Proc: Output file stored
    Proc->>FS: Upload error JSONL (if any)<br/>HTTPS/TLS (S3) or local
    Proc->>PG: Update batch status: completed<br/>Store output_file_id, error_file_id<br/>TCP/TLS
    PG-->>Proc: Confirmed

    Client->>GW: GET /v1/batches/{batch_id}<br/>Tenant: X-MaaS-Username
    GW->>API: Forward request
    API->>PG: Fetch batch record<br/>TCP/TLS
    API->>Redis: Fetch live progress<br/>TCP/TLS
    API-->>Client: 200 OK {status: completed, output_file_id}

    Client->>GW: GET /v1/files/{output_file_id}/content<br/>Tenant: X-MaaS-Username
    GW->>API: Forward request
    API->>FS: Download output file
    API-->>Client: 200 OK (JSONL stream)

    Note over Client,LLM: Flow 2: Batch Cancellation

    Client->>API: POST /v1/batches/{id}/cancel<br/>Tenant: X-MaaS-Username
    API->>Redis: Publish cancel event<br/>(list-based event channel)<br/>TCP/TLS
    Redis-->>API: Published
    API-->>Client: 200 OK {status: cancelling}

    Proc->>Redis: Receive cancel event<br/>(BLMPop listener)<br/>TCP/TLS
    Proc->>Proc: Cancel in-flight requests<br/>(context cancellation)
    Proc->>FS: Upload partial output JSONL
    Proc->>PG: Update status: cancelled<br/>TCP/TLS

    Note over GC,FS: Flow 3: Garbage Collection (periodic)

    GC->>PG: Query expired batches/files<br/>TCP/TLS
    PG-->>GC: Expired records
    GC->>FS: Delete expired file content<br/>HTTPS/TLS (S3) or local
    FS-->>GC: Deleted
    GC->>PG: Delete expired metadata<br/>TCP/TLS
    PG-->>GC: Confirmed
